  "local_port": 39454,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I custom-make my online wedding invitation?",
  "response": "Creating a custom online wedding invitation is a creative and personal way to share your special day with your guests. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide to help you design and send a unique online wedding invitation:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Choose a Platform**\nSelect a platform or tool to create your invitation. Popular options include:\n- **Canva**: Offers customizable templates and design tools.\n- **Paperless Post**: Specializes in elegant digital invitations with RSVP tracking.\n- **Evite**: Provides a variety of customizable e-invitations.\n- **Zola**: A wedding-specific platform for invitations and RSVPs.\n- **Adobe Express**: Great for advanced customization.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Decide on the Design**\n- **Theme and Style**: Reflect your wedding theme (e.g., rustic, modern, vintage, beachy).\n- **Color Palette**: Use colors that match your wedding decor or personal preferences.\n- **Fonts**: Choose fonts that are easy to read and align with your wedding vibe.\n- **Images**: Include engagement photos, illustrations, or graphics.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Craft the Content**\nInclude essential details:\n- **Couple\u2019s Names**: Highlight you and your partner\u2019s names prominently.\n- **Wedding Date and Time**: Be clear and specific.\n- **Location**: Include the venue name and address (or a link to the virtual event if it\u2019s online).\n- **RSVP Information**: Add a link or instructions for RSVPing.\n- **Additional Details**: Dress code, accommodations, registry info, or special instructions.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Add Interactive Elements**\nMake your invitation engaging:\n- **RSVP Button**: Use a platform that allows guests to RSVP directly from the invitation.\n- **Countdown Timer**: Add a timer to create excitement.\n- **Photo Galleries**: Share engagement photos or a video.\n- **Live Links**: Include links to your wedding website, registry, or travel info.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Personalize It**\n- **Custom URL**: Create a unique web address for your invitation (e.g., www.SarahAndJohnWedding.com).\n- **Guest Names**: Personalize invitations with each guest\u2019s name if possible.\n- **Music or Animation**: Add a romantic song or subtle animations for a special touch.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Test and Send**\n- **Preview**: Check how the invitation looks on different devices (desktop, mobile, tablet).\n- **Proofread**: Ensure all details are accurate and error-free.\n- **Send**: Use email, social media, or messaging apps to share the invitation.\n\n---\n\n### **7. Manage RSVPs**\n- **Track Responses**: Use platforms like Zola or Paperless Post to monitor RSVPs.\n- **Send Reminders**: Follow up with guests who haven\u2019t responded.\n\n---\n\nBy customizing your online wedding invitation, you can create a memorable and unique experience for your guests while staying organized and eco-friendly!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
